    <prj:ScienceGoal>
        <prj:name>CO(1-0) detection in the BCG of the A2399 cluster</prj:name>
        <prj:note>We want to detect the CO(1-0) line emission in three spiral galaxies of the Abell cluster A2399 at a distance of ~250 Mpc. The 5 sigma detection of this emission depends on the validity of several assumptions: the Schmidt-Kennicutt' law, the CO-H2 conversion factor and the dust-to-gas ratio. In case of positive detections we can plan future ALMA observations aiming at measuring the mass of the molecular gas in many galaxies of the WINGS survey. These data, when coupled with the SFR measured from the optical spectra, will provide the time scale of gas consumption. Such information, once linked to the properties of the cluster environment, will definitively clarify the role of the environment in quenching the star formation in galaxies. 
In case of a negative detection we can check which hypothesis failed and we can calculate upper limits for the global CO content of our galaxies.</prj:note>
